<lb />Peculiar phrase: <cit><quote>we'll be thy good --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.188" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 188</bibl></cit>; it being a common petitionary phrase to ask a superior to be <emph>good lord</emph> or <emph>good master</emph> to the supplicant. cf. <cit><quote>from my lord Biron, a good m. of mine,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.106" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 106</bibl></cit> (== wellwisher, patron).
